Description of completed labs
Task:
There is an ISP backbone for communication between St. Petersburg and Moscow. Each city has a core router(core router).
Routing must be provided between two clients in different cities, each client is assigned special addresses and AS numbers, and access to the Internet.
This lab required enabling BGP and IS-IS protocols, configuring IPv4 and IPv6 addressing, and implementing simple route-map policy for route filtering.
Special addresses (RFC 5737 & RFC 3849 & RFC 1918) were used for routing between routers and a private AS(RFC 6996) for BGP
